# Paperwork Labs Growth Context (FileFree-focused, pending Phase 6 product split)

## Target Audience
- Gen Z (18-30), especially first-time filers
- 67% report stress about taxes, 44% have already used AI for tax help
- Mobile-first, dark mode, TikTok/Instagram native
- Skeptical of "free" claims (TurboTax burned them), need proof

## Brand Voice
- Smart, calm friend who knows taxes — not software, not the IRS, not a chatbot
- Use "you" and "your." Contractions always. Never "the taxpayer."
- Celebrate wins: "Income section done — nice work."
- Never blame the user for errors
- Anti-TurboTax energy: honest, simple, transparent

## Content Strategy

### SEO (Long-term compounding)
Target keywords:
- "how to file taxes for free 2026"
- "what is a W2 form"
- "standard deduction 2025 amount"
- "first time filing taxes guide"
- "tax refund calculator 2026"

3 articles at launch, add 2/month. Genuinely helpful, not thin SEO bait.

### Social Media (delegated to social.mdc)
Social media execution — platform playbooks, content creation, scheduling, analytics, and paid amplification — lives in social.mdc. Growth owns the strategic direction; Social owns the daily execution.

Key strategic decisions owned by Growth:
- Content pillar priorities (which themes to push this month)
- Ad budget allocation between TikTok Spark Ads and Meta boost
- Creator partnership approvals and budget
- When to shift from tax-season content to year-round financial literacy

### Viral Loops
- Tax receipt card (shareable filing summary) — target 15% share rate
- Referral program with unique codes
- Try-before-signup: the demo IS the marketing

### Paid Amplification (Tax Season Only: $200-500/mo)
- TikTok Spark Ads: boost organic winners (>1K views) for 3-5 day bursts at $20-50/day
- Meta/IG boost: boost top Reels (>500 views) for 2-3 day bursts at $10-30/day
- Strategy: intermittent bursts on proven content, NOT continuous daily ads
- Kill criteria: CPC > $0.50 (TikTok) or $1.00 (Meta) after initial spend = stop
- Off-season: $0 paid. Organic only.

### Creator Partnerships
- Target: personal finance micro-influencers, 10K-100K followers, TikTok/IG
- Terms: free product + rev share via UTM-tracked referral links
- Outreach: 10 DMs/week during pre-launch, convert 2-3 by launch week
- See social.mdc for DM templates and tracking

## Growth Metrics
- Waitlist signups (pre-launch)
- Demo → signup conversion rate
- Filing completion rate
- Share rate (tax receipt card) — target 15%
- Referral conversion rate
- SEO traffic growth (monthly)
- Social: views, completion rate, profile visits, CTR to site
- Paid: CPC, CPM, ROAS per platform

### Revenue-Tied Metrics (post-launch)
- Refund Plan screen view rate (% of filers who see the Refund Plan)
- Refund routing rate (% who allocate to a partner HYSA/IRA) — target 8%
- Financial referral CTR (% who click a recommendation) — target 10-15%
- Financial referral conversion (% who complete partner signup) — target 20-30% of clicks
- Audit Shield attach rate — target 2-4%
- Tax Optimization Plan purchase rate — target 2-5%
- Blended ARPU (target: $8.05 at scale, Scenario B)

## Messaging for Interim E-File
When e-file costs money (before own transmitter is certified):
- Frame as: "We're going through IRS certification. Free e-file coming early 2027."
- Always lead with: "Download your return — free"
- Cost-passthrough messaging: "You pay exactly what we pay. No markup."
- This is a trust-building moment, not a weakness

## Quality Gate (Brand Voice Check)

Before publishing any user-facing copy:
- [ ] Tone matches "smart, calm friend" — not corporate, not robotic
- [ ] Uses "you/your" — never "the taxpayer" or "the user"
- [ ] Contractions used naturally
- [ ] No unsubstantiated claims (e.g., "file in 60 seconds" without proof)
- [ ] Anti-TurboTax positioning is comparative, not aggressive

## Content Review Gate (Mandatory)

Every piece of user-facing content (email, social post, in-app message, landing page copy) must pass this checklist before publishing:

- Brand names spelled correctly (FileFree, LaunchFree -- proper nouns, correct casing)
- "Free" claims are 100% accurate with no hidden conditions
- Tax content uses education framing, not advice ("many do X" not "you should X")
- Legal content uses services framing, not advice
- Circular 230 / UPL disclaimer present where applicable
- FTC affiliate disclosure present if recommending partner products
- CAN-SPAM compliant (unsubscribe, physical address, honest subject line)
- No reference to filefree.com anywhere

